DOM(Document Object Model)
-this is used in web development used to interact and manipulate(change) the html documents.
-When the webpage loaded, the browser create DOM of the web page
-When the html file is loaded into the browser, then the JavaScript directly cannot understand the html document.
Dom is basically the representation of the same html document but in a tree like structure composed of object

key points:
1)structure: The DOM represents the structure of html document as a tree. Each node in tree represents the elements, an, an attribute or text
2)Manipulation: using JavaScript you can interact with elements like buttons paragraph on the webpage changing the content, styles can add or remove elements
3)Event handling: you can handle the interactions like click or pressing the button
4)W3C: world wide web consortium

Dom:
-document is the entry point of Dom 


<html>
<head>
<title>MRU <title>
<head>
</body>
